Enum Constant Detail

SESSION

public static final FlushStrategy SESSION
The session will be flushed. This is the simplest and fastest approach.

OBJECT

public static final FlushStrategy OBJECT
Only changes that affect a specific object will be flushed. In order to do so, all objects except from the one specified will be evicted from the session before flushing and then, they will be re-attached to the session. This is expensive behavior, therefore this flushing policy should be used in rare cases, when it is absolutely necessary. The managed parameter is passed on as a new HashSet containing all the managed entities, so that flush(Object, Session, Set, Set) will not modify it.

EXCLUDING

public static final FlushStrategy EXCLUDING
Changes to session will be flushed, excluding objects that have been marked as excluded. This flushing mode is less expensive than OBJECT, but still heavier than SESSION. The managed parameter is passed on as a new HashSet containing all the managed entities, so that flush(Object, Session, Set, Set) will not modify it.

See Also:
HibernateSessionProvider.setExcluded(Object), HibernateSessionProvider.setNotExcluded(Object)
